"title": "2357: Jesus Christ, parables of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2357: jesus christ, parables of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A central feature of Jesus Christ's teaching was the use of extended similies and short stories about the kingdom of God, based on human experience. Christ used them frequently to call for a response to his message.</p>\n<h2>Parables are a central feature of Jesus Christ's teaching</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:34-Matt13:35\">MAT 13:34–13:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:2\">PSA 78:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:33-Mark4:34\">MRK 4:33–4:34</a></p>\n<h2>Different characteristics of Jesus Christ's parables</h2>\n<h3>They vary in complexity and length</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:6\">MAT 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:18-Matt13:23\">MAT 13:18–13:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:13-Mark4:20\">MRK 4:13–4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:11-Luke8:15\">LUK 8:11–8:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:37-Matt13:45\">MAT 13:37–13:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:52\">MAT 13:52</a></p>\n<h3>They vary in their use of metaphors, word pictures, objects and actions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:13-Matt5:16\">MAT 5:13–5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:44\">MAT 13:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:2-Matt18:3\">MAT 18:2–18:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:18-Matt21:22\">MAT 21:18–21:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:12-Mark11:14\">MRK 11:12–11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:20-Mark11:24\">MRK 11:20–11:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:8-Luke15:10\">LUK 15:8–15:10</a></p>\n<h3>They have different levels of meaning</h3>\n<p>Often the full impact of a parable may be lost if the Jewish context is not understood:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:30-Luke10:37\">LUK 10:30–10:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:11-Luke15:32\">LUK 15:11–15:32</a></p>\n<h3>They draw on human experience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:33\">MAT 13:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:20-Luke13:21\">LUK 13:20–13:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:12-Matt18:14\">MAT 18:12–18:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:4-Luke15:7\">LUK 15:4–15:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:41-Luke7:43\">LUK 7:41–7:43</a></p>\n<h2>The themes of Jesus Christ's parables</h2>\n<h3>The kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:30\">MRK 4:30</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:18\">LUK 13:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:31-Matt13:32\">MAT 13:31–13:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:31-Mark4:32\">MRK 4:31–4:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:19-Luke13:21\">LUK 13:19–13:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:44-Matt13:45\">MAT 13:44–13:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:26-Mark4:29\">MRK 4:26–4:29</a></p>\n<h3>Relationship with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:20\">LUK 15:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:9-Matt7:11\">MAT 7:9–7:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:11-Luke11:13\">LUK 11:11–11:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:12-Matt18:14\">MAT 18:12–18:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:4-Luke15:7\">LUK 15:4–15:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:7-Luke18:8\">LUK 18:7–18:8</a></p>\n<h3>Right behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:37\">LUK 10:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:24-Matt7:27\">MAT 7:24–7:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:47-Luke6:49\">LUK 6:47–6:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:6-Luke13:9\">LUK 13:6–13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:27\">LUK 15:27</a></p>\n<h3>The time of the end</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34\">MAT 25:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1\">MAT 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:19\">MAT 25:14–25:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:11-Luke19:15\">LUK 19:11–19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:35\">MRK 13:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:35-Luke12:36\">LUK 12:35–12:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:40\">LUK 12:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:44\">MAT 24:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:22-Luke16:23\">LUK 16:22–16:23</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ speaks about himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:37\">MAT 21:37</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:6\">MRK 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:13\">LUK 20:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:2\">MAT 22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:10\">MAT 25:10</a>JHN <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:35\">6:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:12\">JHN 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:14\">JHN 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:1\">JHN 15:1</a></p>\n<h2>Understanding Jesus Christ's parables</h2>\n<h3>Further explanation is sometimes needed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:36\">MAT 13:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:18\">MAT 13:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:13\">MRK 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:11\">LUK 8:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:15\">MAT 15:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:17\">MRK 7:17</a></p>\n<h3>The meaning is sometimes hidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:9-Luke8:10\">LUK 8:9–8:10</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:11-Matt13:16\">MAT 13:11–13:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:11-Mark4:12\">MRK 4:11–4:12</a> <em>The meaning of Jesus Christ's parables was concealed only from those whose hearts and minds were closed.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:9-Isa6:10\">ISA 6:9–6:10</a></p>\n<h2>Responses to Jesus Christ's parables</h2>\n<h3>The parables demand action</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:14-Matt5:16\">MAT 5:14–5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:24\">MAT 4:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:5-Matt7:6\">MAT 7:5–7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:43\">MAT 13:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:45-Matt13:46\">MAT 13:45–13:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:13\">MAT 25:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:40\">MAT 25:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:45\">MAT 25:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:21\">LUK 12:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:32-Luke12:33\">LUK 12:32–12:33</a></p>\n<h3>Positive responses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:16\">MAT 13:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:28-Matt7:29\">MAT 7:28–7:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:51\">MAT 13:51</a></p>\n<h3>Rejection of Jesus Christ and his parables</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:19\">LUK 20:19</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:45-Matt21:46\">MAT 21:45–21:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:12\">MRK 12:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:14\">LUK 16:14</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of Jesus Christ's parables</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:1-Matt13:23\">MAT 13:1–13:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:1-Mark4:20\">MRK 4:1–4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:4-Luke8:15\">LUK 8:4–8:15</a> <em>parable of the sower</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:47-Matt13:52\">MAT 13:47–13:52</a> <em>parable of the net</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:12-Matt18:14\">MAT 18:12–18:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:4-Luke15:7\">LUK 15:4–15:7</a> <em>parable of the lost sheep</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:25-Luke10:37\">LUK 10:25–10:37</a> <em>parable of the good Samaritan</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:11-Luke15:32\">LUK 15:11–15:32</a> <em>parable of the lost son</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a> <em>parable of the Pharisee and the tax collector</em></p>",
